 Not even higher level evacs touch lower level characters... so I doubt they &quot;forgot&quot; bards. No heals above 50 land on sub46 chars. No buffs.... no nothing.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
that would be a really dumb way to fix the &quot;problem&quot;. A level 52 could easily group with a level 44 for xp under normal legitimate grouping. If they're going to do something like that, the lower level limit should be the lowest level that could get xp with a 51 (level 34). <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nicolheartsbane>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 989<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 1:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Q about tomorrow's patch</span><hr size=1> It sounds like that should have failed testing, then.  Good change, so I would like it to be fixed promptly.<br>
<br>
I think every 50+ spell needs a recommended/required level.<br>
<br>
I should be able to cast levitation on anyone that I can levitate.  A paladin should be able to cast the same heal on someone that a cleric can.  Many of the lower 50's buffs should legitimately land on some group members on whom they would not currently land.<br>
<br>
Are they just bringing back the old bugs they fixed when they originally eased the buffing restrictions?<br>
<br>
I now see that recommended levels might be needed also, because a heal spell should never completely fail because it is &quot;too powerful&quot;.  That's like saying I can't kill an orc pawn with ice comet.<br>
<br>
Wait, bad example ...<br>
